        "headline": "USN-8066-1: Rack vulnerabilities",
        "content": {
          "excerpt_text": "Minh Pham Quang discovered that Rack did not correctly handle parsing certain paths, which could lead to a path traversal attack. An attacker could possibly use this issue to leak sensitive information. (CVE-2026-22860) Ali Firas discovered that Rack did not correctly sanitize certain inputs. An attacker could possibly use this issue to execute arbitrary code. (CVE-2026-25500)",
          "lang": "en"
        },
        "provenance": {
